  <properties>
    <title>Filter reads step</title>
    <author email="jourdren@biologie.ens.fr">Laurent Jourdren</author> 
  </properties> 



  <body>
  
    <section name="Filter reads step">

      <p>This step allow to filter input reads. Currently, this step can trim polyN read tails, remove reads with a short length
and discard reads with bad base quality mean.</p>  

      <ul>
 	<li><b>Internal name</b>: filterreads</li> 
        <li><b>Available</b>: Both local and distributed mode.</li>
 	<li><b>Input</b>: Fastq or tfq file</li>
	<li><b>Output</b>: filtered fastq or filtered tfq file (e.g. <code>filtered_reads_1.fq</code>).</li>

	<br/>
        <li><b>Optional parameters</b>:</li>
	<table>
		<tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Value</th><th>Description</th><th>Default value</th></tr>
		<tr><td>lengthThreshold</td><td>integer</td><td>The threshold for the length of the reads. Unit in bases.</td><td>15</td></tr>
		<tr><td>qualityThreshold</td><td>float</td><td>The threshold for the mean base quality. Unit in decimal quality score.</td><td>15.0</td></tr>
		<!--tr><td>pairedend</td><td>boolean</td><td>True to enable paired-end mode</td></tr-->
	</table>
      </ul>
      
    </section>


  </body>
  
